<subSubSection pageId="27" pageNumber="28" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1437,1399,1874]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,379,1399,1425]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Diagnosis of male.</emphasis>
The male of this species is easily recognized by the triangular shaped posterior margin of the head, the weakly excised mandibles that are oblique apically (
<figureCitation box="[926,1014,1437,1463]" captionStart="FIGURES 25 – 31" captionStartId="13.[151,274,1360,1384]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,194,1326]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1436,194,1338]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 25 – 31. Head, anterior view. 25. Sphaeropthalma. megagnathos; 26. S. mendica; 27. S. pallida; 28. S. sublobata; 29. S. tetracuspis; 30. S. triangularis; and 31. S. yumaella." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/196850/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
Fig. 
<number box="[981,1014,1437,1463]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" value="30.0">30</number>
</figureCitation>
), the lack of mesosternal processes, the lobe-like projections on the hind coxae, and the triangulate posterior projection of the apex of the hind tibia. The genitalia are illustrated by Pitts 
<emphasis box="[642,701,1512,1537]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">et al.</emphasis>
(
<number box="[716,778,1512,1538]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" value="2009.0">2009</number>
) in 
<figureCitation box="[824,910,1512,1538]" captionStart="FIGURES 25 – 31" captionStartId="13.[151,274,1360,1384]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,194,1326]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1436,194,1338]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 25 – 31. Head, anterior view. 25. Sphaeropthalma. megagnathos; 26. S. mendica; 27. S. pallida; 28. S. sublobata; 29. S. tetracuspis; 30. S. triangularis; and 31. S. yumaella." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/196850/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
Fig. 
<number box="[877,910,1512,1538]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" value="26.0">26</number>
</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1437,1399,1874]" box="[197,1181,1549,1575]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
